  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed vehicular crossover, by reason of the inadequate depth of the front drive, would result in the risk of vehicles overhanging the public footway, degrading the level of service for pedestrians and also the efficiency of the highway network, resulting in highway safety concerns, contrary to Policies T4 and T6 of the London Plan, Policy 24 of the London Borough of Havering Local Plan, the Havering Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD and the NPPF.",
    "The proposed vehicular crossover would adversely effect the character, quality and appearance of the existing green amenity area, which currently forms part of the character and appearance of this part of Dagnam Park Drive and the wider estate, which would be detrimental to the character of the streetscene and likely to set an undesirable precedent for future development, contrary to the provisions of Policy 24 of the London Borough of Havering Local Plan, the Havering Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD and the NPPF",
